      <h1 class='title'>Gas Desulphurisation Plant</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 21 January 2004 vol 416 c60WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_60ws' title='Col. 60WS &mdash; HC Deb 21 January 2004 vol 416 c60WS' name='column_60ws' href='#column_60ws' rel='bookmark'>60WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0416P2_20040121_CWS_3'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-stephen-timms' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0416P2_20040121_CWS_3' title='Link to this speech by Mr Stephen Timms' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-stephen-timms" title="Mr Stephen Timms">The Minister for Energy, E-Commerce and Postal Services (Mr. Stephen Timms)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">I have today granted consent under Section 36 of the <a href="/acts/electricity-act-1989">Electricity Act 1989</a> to Rugeley Power Limited for the construction of flue gas desulphurisation plant at the 1,000 MW coal-fired power station at Rugeley in Staffordshire. Planning permission for the plant has also been deemed to be granted, subject to 47 planning conditions agreed with the Staffordshire County Council, the Cannock Chase District Council and the Lichfield District Council.</p><p>Copies of the press notice and decision letter are being placed in the Library of the House.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
